ies in three dimensions: in terms of epistemology, as forms of needs-based thinking; and in terms of worldviews.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aIdeologie (Begriff). 4aPhilosophie /Erkenntnistheorie. 4aPolitische Philosophie. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Methodology.2bisacsh  aIdeology (Concept).  aPhilosophy/Epistemology.  aPolitical Philosophy.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Philosophy 2000 - 2014z9783110636949oZDB-23-GPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2012z9783110288995oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET PHILOSOPHIE  2012z9783110294040oZDB-23-DPH0 cprintz978311019051940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311022727740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110227277423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110227277/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2012  aZDB-23-DPHb2012  aZDB-23-GPHc2000d2014